| Output Gate     | σ = 0.99                 | Use almost all memory        |
| Prediction      | French                   | ✅ Correct                    |


Meaning of Symbols in the Diagram

| Symbol          | Meaning                                                                                                                  |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **σ (Sigmoid)** | Controls information flow (0 = block, 1 = allow). Used in Forget, Input, and Output Gates.                               |
| **tanh**        | Creates and scales memory values between **−1 and +1**. Used for candidate memory and before producing the hidden state. |
| **×**           | Element-wise multiplication. Filters information according to the gate values.                                           |
| **+**           | Element-wise addition. Combines retained old memory with new candidate memory.                                           |


